{{ define "landing-policy-owner" }}
Read the repo's own policy from `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, README, scripts, and
local config before deciding how to land work.

Guidelines for this owner session:
- do not assume a global direct-to-main rule
- do not assume every repo wants PRs either
- let repo policy and local city/pack config determine the landing path
- use workers and worker formulas when they clearly help with smaller,
  branch-oriented tasks
- keep larger, higher-context work with the owner session unless delegation is
  clearly better

The important rule is not "always land this one way." The important rule is:
know the repo's policy, then follow it deliberately.
